  <main class="pt-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
      <h1 class="mb-8 font-mono text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight">Refund Policy</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-[#a1a1a1]">
        <section>
          <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> 2026-02-08</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">1. Statutory Right of Withdrawal (EU/EEA Consumers)</h2>
          <p>If you are a consumer in the EU/EEA and purchase GDAgent online, you generally have a <strong>14-day right of withdrawal</strong> for distance contracts.</p>
          <p><strong>Exception for digital content:</strong> The right of withdrawal expires early if you expressly agree that we begin performance before the end of the withdrawal period and acknowledge that you thereby lose your right of withdrawal (Directive 2011/83/EU; implemented in national law).</p>
          <p>If the right of withdrawal applies, you can withdraw within 14 days without giving any reason. The withdrawal period begins on the day of contract conclusion.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">2. Voluntary 30-Day Money-Back Guarantee</h2>
          <p>Independent of your statutory rights, we offer a <strong>30-day money-back guarantee</strong> from the date of purchase.</p>
          <p>A refund under this voluntary guarantee is available if:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The Software does not work as described, and</li>
            <li>We cannot resolve the issue within a reasonable timeframe.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">3. Exclusions</h2>
          <p>Refunds may be denied if:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The license has been used in violation of the Terms.</li>
            <li>The request is fraudulent or abusive.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">4. Refund Process</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Contact support at <a href="mailto:gdagent@protonmail.com" class="text-white hover:underline">gdagent@protonmail.com</a> with your order details.</li>
            <li>We may attempt to troubleshoot the issue.</li>
            <li>If unresolved and eligible, we will approve the refund through Lemon Squeezy.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">5. What to Include in Your Request</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Your order ID (from the Lemon Squeezy receipt)</li>
            <li>The email address used for purchase</li>
            <li>A short description of the issue</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We typically respond within 48 hours.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">6. License Deactivation</h2>
          <p>Approved refunds result in license deactivation via the Lemon Squeezy license system.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">7. Refund Method and Timing</h2>
          <p>Refunds are processed by Lemon Squeezy and returned to the original payment method. Processing times depend on your payment provider and may take several business days.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-medium text-white">8. Statutory Rights Unaffected</h2>
          <p>This Refund Policy does not limit any mandatory statutory rights you may have under applicable consumer protection laws.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
